node.text: Music teacher @kirstymarie23’s New York studio is remarkably functional and cozy despite the small size! node.text: Today’s One Good Thing at Home is all about setting yourself up for cleaning success. This simple, eco-friendly under-sink cleaning setup has been Maxwell’s go-to lately! Shop the products via the link in our bio. 🧽  #OneGoodThingAtHome

node.text:
@rachel_tower_house’s 150-year-old home in the Scottish highlands used to be a church, and she retained all of the original architectural features. We’re talking arched windows, striking moldings, and a spiral staircase situation you simply MUST. SEE. Get a full tour at the link in our bio. 

(Image & Home: @rachel_tower_house)

node.text:
Kailee’s modern farmhouse-style condo beautifully blends old and new. “Our condo is only 588 square feet, so I wanted to pack a lot of personality into a small space. I painted the kitchen cabinets, bathroom vanity, and walls to make it more us,” she says. Make sure to check out the magnificent blue kitchen at the link in our bio. 

(Image: Rhonda Farnham; Home: Kailee Ryan)
